The paper focuses on high-resolution representation learning for vision problems, such as pose estimation, semantic segmentation, facial landmark detection, and object detection. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also introduces a modification to the existing high-resolution network, which can be considered a machine learning technique, leading to the possibility of it being categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper applies the proposed approach to various vision tasks, which can be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, the paper also mentions the use of Faster R-CNN object detection framework, which can be categorized under cs.MM (Multimedia).
